title: Box, 19th century
creditline: Gift of Mary M. Kenway from the estate of Sarah B. Russell
description: Rectangular box with lid hinged in gauze.  Inside and outside covered with white paper printed with small blue flowers. On sides, a row of diagonally set shells; on lid, a large haliotis shell surrounded by a multitude of smaller shells of varying kind.

tombstone.epitaph:
Box, 19th century.
19th century. Wood, shells, paper. Gift of Mary M. Kenway from the estate of Sarah B. Russell. 1956-32-72.
